==================================================
NEURALFORGE ENGINEERING CONSTITUTION
==================================================


# Identity

NeuralForge is an autonomous desktop AI development environment designed to become a Cursor-level IDE replacement.

Architecture:

- Tauri desktop shell
- Rust backend
- Next.js frontend
- React
- TypeScript
- Monaco Editor
- SQLite persistence
- AI model routing
- Repository indexing
- Autonomous engineering workflows


Operating principle:

UNDERSTAND FIRST.

MODIFY SECOND.

VALIDATE ALWAYS.


==================================================

# Source Of Truth

When information conflicts:

Priority:

1. Repository files.
2. Automated tests.
3. Git history.
4. Documentation.
5. Previous AI conversations.


Never assume previous AI output is correct.


==================================================

# Development Rules

Before changing files:

Explain:

CHANGE:

WHY:

FILES:

RISK:

EXPECTED RESULT:


After changes:

Provide:

FILES CHANGED:

IMPLEMENTATION:

VALIDATION:

RESULT:


==================================================

# No Silent Mutation

Never silently:

- edit files
- create files
- install dependencies
- change configuration
- modify tests


==================================================

# Testing Rules

Never:

- delete failing tests
- weaken assertions
- skip validation
- hide failures


All changes require validation.


Rust:

cargo test


Frontend:

npm run build

tsc --noEmit


==================================================
# FROZEN ARCHITECTURE PROTECTION
==================================================

The following files represent protected NeuralForge foundation systems.

They must not be modified without explicit Level 5 approval.

Protected files:

src-tauri/src/agent/executor.rs

src-tauri/src/agent/planner.rs

src-tauri/src/database/indexer.rs

src-tauri/src/database/search.rs

src-tauri/src/database/resolver.rs

src-tauri/src/extensions/


Protected concepts:

- execution safety pipeline
- snapshot/apply/verify/rollback behavior
- AI planning behavior
- repository indexing behavior
- semantic search behavior
- workspace resolution behavior
- extension architecture


If a change appears necessary:

STOP.

Generate:

CHANGE REQUEST:

WHY REQUIRED:

EXPECTED BENEFIT:

POSSIBLE REGRESSION:

ALTERNATIVES:

ROLLBACK PLAN:


Wait for explicit approval before editing.


==================================================
END FROZEN ARCHITECTURE PROTECTION
==================================================

# Dependency Rules

Before adding packages:

Report:

Package:

Reason:

Alternative:

Security impact:

Build impact:


Never automatically upgrade major dependencies.


==================================================

# Change Classification


LEVEL 0:

Documentation.


LEVEL 1:

Small isolated fixes.


LEVEL 2:

Normal features.


LEVEL 3:

Shared systems.

Requires analysis.


LEVEL 4:

Architecture changes.

Requires approval.


LEVEL 5:

Core redesign.

Requires explicit approval.


==================================================

# AI Model Responsibilities


DeepSeek Coding Model:

Used for:

- implementation
- debugging
- file editing
- testing


Reasoning Models:

Used for:

- architecture
- major planning
- complex debugging


Local Models:

Used for:

- quick searches
- explanations
- lightweight tasks


==================================================

# Token Efficiency

Before reading large files:

Explain why.


Avoid:

- duplicate context
- unnecessary scans
- rewriting existing documentation


Use the smallest required context.


==================================================

# Engineering Reports

Every task ends with:


STATUS:

DISCOVERY:

ROOT CAUSE:

PLAN:

FILES AFFECTED:

RISK:

IMPLEMENTATION:

VALIDATION:

RESULT:

NEXT STEP:


==================================================

# Git Protection

Never:

- rebase
- squash
- rewrite history


Protect existing commits.


==================================================
END CONSTITUTION
==================================================
